  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "Namco Anthology is a 1998 duology of video game compilations developed and released by Namco for the PlayStation exclusively in Japan. The two collections compile several Namco-published video games for the Family Computer, Super Famicom, and Mega Drive, in a manner similar to the company's existing Namco Museum series. Alongside ports of the original games are remakes of each game that feature enhanced graphics, sound, and gameplay.",
